Old quarrels, the new Middle East
The ceasefire between Israel and Hamas is still a failure for peace.
Will there ever be lasting peace between Arabs and Jews in the Middle East?
Another bloodshed suggests that such hope is in vain.
While the same futile arguments remain for who began, dozens of buildings have been reduced to dust; more than 140 Palestinians, most of them were civilians, and six Israelis were killed; and, for the first time, rockets fired from Gaza landed near Tel Aviv, the metropolis of Israel, and the Holy City of Jerusalem.
